  "prompt": "What are the best documentary websites?",
  "response": "There are several great websites where you can find high-quality documentaries. Here are some of the best options:\n\n1. **Netflix**:\n   - Offers a broad selection of documentaries covering various topics, from nature and science to history and social issues.\n\n2. **Hulu**:\n   - Provides access to a wide variety of documentaries, with a focus on contemporary issues and popular culture.\n\n3. **Amazon Prime Video**:\n   - Features a substantial collection of documentaries, including exclusives and critically acclaimed films.\n\n4. **PBS Documentaries**:\n   - Known for high-quality, in-depth documentaries on a range of topics including history, science, and social issues.\n\n5. **CuriosityStream**:\n   - A streaming service dedicated solely to documentaries, covering science, technology, history, and nature.\n\n6. **National Geographic**:\n   - Offers renowned documentaries with stunning visuals and educational content, focusing mainly on nature, science, and exploration.\n\n7. **Discovery+**:\n   - Hosts a vast array of documentaries from the Discovery Channel and its affiliates, including topics like wildlife, adventure, and lifestyle.\n\n8. **The Criterion Channel**:\n   - Features classic and high-quality contemporary documentaries, often curated alongside feature films.\n\n9. **Kanopy**:\n   - A free service available through libraries and universities, offering a wide range of educational documentaries.\n\n10. **Vimeo**:\n   - Provides access to independent documentaries and short films, often with unique perspectives and creative approaches.\n\n11. **YouTube**:\n   - Hosts countless documentaries, from independent creators to full-length features uploaded by studios and broadcasters.\n\n12. **Docuseek**:\n   - Specializes in educational documentaries, offering films from various collections suited for teachers and students.\n\n13. **Society.tv**:\n   - Features trending documentaries and unique storytelling.\n\nKeep in mind that some of these services require subscriptions or may be available through partnerships with libraries or educational institutions.",
